<subSubSection id="71005B6FF0C0C97E3B76F300EADDD703" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B7ED8366B2332EE90F5EA04660CBE730" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD5901C5FB537E4FC03071DCC9C068C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="2C486842D126D451289078B963A77263" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Potamanthidae" genus="Rhoenanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhoenanthus speciosus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="9B93FBFE80F4614E8709025CE5CF7241" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Rhoenanthus speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of other 
<taxonomicName id="431190DD18C6F30AAD9D1B1C2467DC6B" authority="(Rhoenanthus)" class="Insecta" family="Potamanthidae" genus="Rhoenanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhoenanthus (Rhoenanthus)" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Rhoenanthus">Rhoenanthus (Rhoenanthus)</taxonomicName>
species based on the following characteristics: i) lateral subapical spine of the mandibular tusk present (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8049C6746DD0427C29B8E4C252BF44BC" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Larval morphology (head and mandibular tusk) A Potamanthus formosus Eaton, 1892 B Rhoenanthus magnificus Ulmer, 1920 C R. obscurus Navas, 1922 D angle measurement of mandibular tusk E R. distafurcus Bae &amp; McCafferty, 1991 F R. speciosus Eaton, 1881." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1067.72779.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/604591" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">10F</figureCitation>
), ii) absence of medial rounded setae on the mandibular tusk, iii) length of the mandibular tusks ca 1.7-2.3
<normalizedToken id="4C0E8085C8A8997EC262F2975241A545" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of the head, iv) length of the foretibiae ca 1.2-1.23
<normalizedToken id="675123BEE5B4EF34A5FBBB27EA5A5D48" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of the forefemora and about 2.72-2.82
<normalizedToken id="19B6966FE9F162929483B174432BD859" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of the foretarsi, v) leg with colour marking as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CE38AD1431A08AEB4219F827855B377C" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Larval morphology (foreleg) A Potamanthus formosus Eaton, 1892 B Rhoenanthus magnificus Ulmer, 1920 C R. obscurus Navas, 1922 D R. distafurcus Bae &amp; McCafferty, 1991 E R. speciosus Eaton, 1881. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1067.72779.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/604592" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">11E, and vi</figureCitation>
) 4 or 5 bipectinated lateral setae on the mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="1841F0250B93A6813875198A048DEF91" author="Bae, YJ" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B1" refString="Bae, YJ, McCafferty, WP, 1991. Phylogenetic Systematics of the Potamanthidae (Ephemeroptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 117(3/4): 1-143." title="Phylogenetic Systematics of the Potamanthidae (Ephemeroptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 117 (3 / 4): 1 - 143." year="1991">Bae and McCafferty 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73CEE0D0F5CAB386EFF8F728663432BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="3D5D98B10970BF18EDACFEF4E010F4FE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Egg</emphasis>
(dissected from mature larva). Oval; with two large conical polar caps, (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CC53BEE3DBACB6CCCA9022D5B349C828" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. SEMs of egg structures of Rhoenanthus speciosus Eaton, 1881 A general outline of egg B micropyle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1067.72779.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/604594" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">13A</figureCitation>
); chorion with numerous scattered tubercles, with knob-terminated coiled threads at the equatorial zone; tagenoform micropyle; sperm guide circular (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F24AFA8C5550994B86F426730BFC7788" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. SEMs of egg structures of Rhoenanthus speciosus Eaton, 1881 A general outline of egg B micropyle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1067.72779.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/604594" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">13B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F79FDB1F2E97F66E92564FE888AB260A" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="843212C257759D91AC716CE770C0B7D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="08943B915C45AF29FD4CFE359C8ACA8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Narathiwat and Songkla provinces.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C91F04A345E624D6E364036C3465017C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="A1AC90148B81497900555181B7ECF55E" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5EDFF736B948913FD8A96733167A9B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="18D22F1DB827E29D6251AC200D7960E5" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Potamanthidae" genus="Rhoenanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhoenanthus speciosus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="0794A85D68FF76665BE22D1D14DE039F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Rhoenanthus speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="C9C80474AFB2C10B634E69439412AB7A" author="Bae, YJ" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B1" refString="Bae, YJ, McCafferty, WP, 1991. Phylogenetic Systematics of the Potamanthidae (Ephemeroptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 117(3/4): 1-143." title="Phylogenetic Systematics of the Potamanthidae (Ephemeroptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 117 (3 / 4): 1 - 143." year="1991">Bae and McCafferty (1991)</bibRefCitation>
based on specimens from Indonesia and Malaysia. 
<bibRefCitation id="BFBA453B00337EBC69FB7983422BFBED" author="Parnrong, S" journalOrPublisher="Science Asia" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 409" refId="B18" refString="Parnrong, S, Buathong, M, Sites, RW, 2002. New records of Behningiidae, Potamanthidae, and Prosopistomatidae (Ephemeroptera) from Thailand. Science Asia 28: 407 - 409" title="New records of Behningiidae, Potamanthidae, and Prosopistomatidae (Ephemeroptera) from Thailand." volume="28" year="2002">Parnrong et al. (2002)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from Songkhla province (southern Thailand). In the present study, we found the larva of this species in the nearby Narathiwat province. The distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="B1CAF74F7EF5561E48A488F70EC14386" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. speciosus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="3B150CD31E68ED15AE6561505F94F48F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">R. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be restricted to the south of the Isthmus of Kra, as was found for another mayfly species, 
<taxonomicName id="6504288D0DFD1240261B5F5D84AB9823" authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Prosopistomatidae" genus="Prosopistoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosopistoma wouterae" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wouterae">
<emphasis id="0B2A35AA89334A1B25F7BD0D5B3346EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Prosopistoma wouterae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Boonsoong &amp; Sartori, 2019). These findings constitute the northern limit of the known distribution of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
